Install Raspbian via NOOBS installer [https://www.raspberrypi.org/downloads/noobs/]

Configure Raspbian System

Go through initial setup (wifi, etc), change default password

Open Terminal

sudo raspi-config

5 -> Interfacing Options
Enable VNC
Enable SSH
(also enabled spi, i2c, may need them in the futrue)


Local System:
Install RealVNC Viewer

Can now configure remotely.



sudo apt install gedit

sudo apt install libftdi-dev
sudo pip3 install pylibftdi
sudo pip3 install pi_sht1x

https://pylibftdi.readthedocs.io/en/0.15.0/installation.html





Wiring:

USB Relay: FTDI (when facing) Left: NC, Center: VCC, Right: NOOBS

SHT1xx: 


Dev Environment:
VSCode
libftdi-dev
Python3
pip3
    pylibftdi
    pi_sht1x
ssh client
scp client
vnc client